      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WARATAH LAD (6) flew the lids off the inside draw with a fast early split and gave a sight, finishing a 5.5 lengths second (22.79) over 400m at this track. Overdue and is among the main hopes. PAW YARIS (3) scored her maiden success two back but safely held last time when seventh and beaten 6 lengths at Warragul over 400m (23.12) last time. Has placed one times at this track. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. I'M TO BLAME (1) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only half a length (22.49) behind Paw Ballista at Ballarat. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Can measure up. RING A DIOR (8) has definite claims at her first try at this circuit.",
